ue:** $18,674 million\n*   **Space Revenue:** $4,086 million **(~21.9%)**\n*   **Connectivity Revenue:** $11,387 million **(~61.0%)**\n*   **AI Revenue:** $3,201 million **(~17.1%)**\n\n**Year Ended December 31, 2024:**\n*   **Total Revenue:** $14,015 million\n*   **Space Revenue:** $3,796 million **(~27.1%)**\n*   **Connectivity Revenue:** $7,599 million **(~54.2%)**\n*   **AI Revenue:** $2,620 million **(~18.7%)**\n\n**Year Ended December 31, 2023:**\n*   **Total Revenue:** $10,387 million\n*   **Space Revenue:** $3,557 million **(~34.2%)**\n*   **Connectivity Revenue:** $3,869 million **(~37.2%)**\n*   **AI Revenue:** $2,961 million **(~28.5%)**\n\n**Key Trend:** Connectivity (Starlink) has become the dominant revenue segment, growing from 37% in 2023 to 61% in 2025. The Space segment's share has decreased proportionally, while the AI segment's share has remained relatively stable despite absolute growth.\n\n### 3. Concentration of Backlog and Deferred Revenue\nThe notes provide **total consolidated figures** for deferred revenue and backlog but **do not disclose a segment-level breakdown**.\n\n*   **Deferred Revenue:**\n    *   As of December 31, 2025: **$12,116 million**\n    *   As of March 31, 2026: **$13,236 million**\n    *   **Primary Drivers:** Space agreements and Connectivity enterprise and government contracts.\n\n*   **Backlog (Performance Obligations):**\n    *   As of December 31, 2025: **$28,377 million** (of which $12,116 million was deferred revenue).\n    *   As of March 31, 2026: **$27,621 million** (of which $13,236 million was deferred revenue).\n    *   **Recognition Timeline (as of March 31, 2026):** ~36% expected within one year, ~46% between one and three years, and ~18% thereafter.\n\n**Conclusion:** While the growth of the Connectivity segment is the main story for overall revenue, the Space segment is strategically reorienting its revenue mix towards development work (for both internal use and government contracts) and investing heavily in the next-generation Starship system to enable future growth for the entire company. The backlog is substantial but its concentration by segment is not disclosed.",
